radiographic_examinations.findings: A retrocecal appendix identified in the right lower quadrant, abnormally distended and fluid-filled, measuring 20 mm in maximal diameter. Appendiceal wall circumferentially thickened with periappendiceal fat stranding and edema. Small amount of fluid lateral and posterior to the appendix, suspicious for possible early perforation. No abscess identified. Remainder of the bowel unremarkable. Gravid uterus identified; no placental or uterine abnormalities. Normal ovaries. Collapsed bladder. No pelvic or inguinal lymphadenopathy. No suspicious focal bone marrow signal abnormalities.
